1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with modeling functions defined over strings, which is a common problem in natural language processing. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a neural network-based model and learning algorithm. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with modeling and learning complex structures from data. 
4. cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as weighted finite automata have applications in speech recognition and synthesis. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also less likely but possible as the paper proposes a new model and learning algorithm for a specific type of automaton.
